2C%20activist%2C%20documentary%20maker%20and%20a%20legend%20for%20many%20news%20reporters%20and%20news%20analysts%2C%20is%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20family%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fjohnpilger%2Fstatus%2F1741419322449215716%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eannounced%20his%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20with%20great%20sadness%20the%20family%20of%20John%20Pilger%20announce%20he%20died%20yesterday%2030%20December%202023%20in%20London%20aged%2084.%20His%20journalism%20and%20documentaries%20were%20celebrated%20around%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20to%20his%20family%20he%20was%20simply%20the%20most%20amazing%20and%20loved%20Dad%2C%20Grandad%20and%20partner.%20Rest%20In%20Peace.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia-born%20Pilger%20was%20adversarial%2C%20feisty%20and%20uncompromising%2C%20drawing%20praise%20and%20respect%20from%20people%20across%20the%20ideological%20fence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjohnpilger.com%2Fbiography%5C%22%3EPilger%20was%20born%20and%20grew%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Bondi%2C%20Sydney%2C%20Australia.%20His%20website%20confirms%20that%20he%20launched%20his%20first%20newspaper%20at%20Sydney%20High%20School%20and%20later%20completed%20a%20four%20year%20cadetship%20with%20Australian%20Consolidated%20Press.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20one%20of%20the%20strictest%20language%20courses%20I%20know%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20%E2%80%9CDevised%20by%20a%20celebrated%2C%20literate%20editor%2C%20Brian%20Penton%2C%20the%20aim%20was%20economy%20of%20language%20and%20accuracy.%20It%20certainly%20taught%20me%20to%20admire%20writing%20that%20was%20spare%2C%20precise%20and%20free%20of%20cliches%2C%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20retreat%20into%20the%20passive%20voice%20and%20used%20adjectives%20only%20when%20absolutely%20necessary.%20I%20have%20long%20since%20slipped%20that%20leash%2C%20but%20those%20early%20disciplines%20helped%20shape%20my%20journalism%20and%20writing%20and%20my%20understanding%20of%20moving%20and%20still%20pictures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20of%20his%20Australian%20generation%2C%20Pilger%20and%20two%20colleagues%20left%20for%20Europe%20in%20the%20early%201960s.%20He%20has%20been%20mostly%20based%20in%20the%20UK%20since%201962.%20According%20to%20Pilger%E2%80%99s%20official%20website%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20set%20up%20an%20ill-fated%20freelance%20%E2%80%98agency%E2%80%99%20in%20Italy%20(with%20the%20grand%20title%20of%20%E2%80%98Interep%E2%80%99)%20and%20quickly%20went%20broke.%20Arriving%20in%20London%2C%20Pilger%20freelanced%2C%20then%20joined%20Reuters%2C%20moving%20to%20the%20London%20Daily%20Mirror%2C%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20selling%20newspaper%2C%20which%20was%20then%20changing%20to%20a%20serious%20tabloid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20became%20chief%20foreign%20correspondent%20and%20reported%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20covering%20numerous%20wars%2C%20notably%20Vietnam.%20Still%20in%20his%20twenties%2C%20he%20became%20the%20youngest%20journalist%20to%20receive%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20highest%20award%20for%20journalism%2C%C2%A0Journalist%20of%20the%20Year%C2%A0and%20was%20the%20first%20to%20win%20it%20twice.%20Moving%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20he%20reported%20the%20upheavals%20there%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20and%201970s.%20He%20marched%20with%20America%E2%80%99s%20poor%20from%20Alabama%20to%20Washington%2C%20following%20the%20assassination%20of%20Martin%20Luther%20King.%20He%20was%20in%20the%20same%20room%20when%20Robert%20Kennedy%2C%20the%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20was%20assassinated%20in%20June%201968.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20work%20in%20South%20East%20Asia%20produced%20an%20iconic%20issue%20of%20the%20London%20Mirror%2C%20devoted%20almost%20entirely%20to%20his%20world%20exclusive%20dispatches%20from%20Cambodia%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Pol%20Pot%E2%80%99s%20reign.%20The%20combined%20impact%20of%20his%C2%A0Mirror%C2%A0reports%20and%20his%20subsequent%20documentary%2C%C