20I%20soon%20found%20out%20that%20it's%20all%20about%20having%20a%20good%20credit%20score%20and%20a%20favorable%20debt-to-income%20ratio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20choosing%20a%20lender%20for%20my%20first%20FHA%20property%20in%202008%2C%20I%20discussed%20my%20intentions%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgage-broker%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emultiple%20mortgage%20brokers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20recommended%20by%20my%20real-estate%20agent%20and%20landed%20with%20one%20who%20I%20felt%20understood%20my%20situation%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20educated%20me%20through%20the%20process%20as%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-and-advice-for-first-time-homebuyer-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20first-time%20homebuyer.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20felt%20comfortable%2C%20was%20informed%20rather%20than%20rushed%2C%20and%20wasn't%20treated%20as%20just%20another%20number%20in%20a%20broker's%20book%20of%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20identify%20how%20much%20I%20could%20borrow%20and%20determine%20my%20lendability%2C%20I%20provided%20my%20broker%20with%20the%20necessary%20documentation%2C%20which%20included%20my%20credit%20score%2C%20pay%20stubs%2C%20tax%20returns%2C%20and%20income%20from%20my%20W-2%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20process%20can%20be%20grueling.%20You'll%20most%20likely%20have%20to%20submit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20resubmit%20%E2%80%94%20updated%20bank%20statements%2C%20pay%20stubs%2C%20and%20other%20miscellaneous%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'd%20submitted%20my%20paperwork%2C%20my%20broker%20was%20able%20to%20source%20the%20best%20options%20for%20me%20at%20the%20time%2C%20which%20was%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-caused-the-great-recession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esubprime%20mortgage%20financial%20crisis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0My%20broker%20ended%20up%20sourcing%20an%20FHA%20and%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F203k-loan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20FHA%20203(k)%20loan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Wells%20Fargo.%20While%20an%20FHA%20loan%20is%20a%20government-backed%20mortgage%2C%20an%20FHA%20203(k)%20loan%20is%20a%20type%20of%20FHA%20loan%20that's%20specifically%20meant%20for%20home%20renovations%20or%20repairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20FHA%20203(k)%20allows%20borrowers%20to%20roll%20the%20cost%20of%20their%20home%20improvements%20into%20their%20mortgage%20by%20borrowing%20up%20to%20110%25%20of%20the%20home's%20value%20after%20the%20improvements%20are%20made%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20was%20straight%20out%20of%20college%20%E2%80%94%20with%20piling%20college%20debt%20but%20no%20credit%20cards%20or%20car%20payments%2C%20minimal%20savings%2C%20and%20W-2%20income%20that%20was%20less%20than%20a%20year%20established%2C%20I%20was%20the%20ideal%20candidate%20for%20an%20FHA%20loan%20with%20the%20guidelines%20that%20existed%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Give%20yourself%20clear%20criteria%20for%20a%20home%20purchase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20evaluated%20my%20first%20owner-occupied%20property%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20several%20important%20factors%20that%20have%20remained%20relevant.%20The%20first%20was%20potential%20locations%20%E2%80%94%20I%20looked%20for%20neighborhoods%20with%20good%20schools%2C%20transportation%2C%20low%20crime%20rates%2C%20and%20rent%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20I%20considered%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20property.%20Properties%20that%20are%20structurally%20sound%20but%20require%20cosmetic%20updates%20may%20come%20at%20a%20higher%20cost.%20However%2C%20distressed%20properties%20that%20require%20significant%20repairs%20might%20be%20more%20affordable%20but%20require%20a%20budget%20to%20make%20them%20safe%2C%20comfortable%2C%20and%20rent-ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20I%20examined%20the%20particular%20property%20type%2C%20such%20as%20duplex%2C%20triplex%2C%20or%20quadplex.%20A%20traditional%20FHA%20loan%20limits%20you%20to%20two%20to%20four%20units.%20It%20wasn't%20long%20until%20I%20identified%20my%20first%20property%3A%20a%20very%20small%20two-family%20property%2C%20each%20with%20one%20bedroom%20and%20one%20bathroom%2C%20in%20a%20middle-class%20area%20listed%20for%20%24115%2C000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20home%20was%20a%20throwback%20to%201970%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20update%20everything%20through%20my%20own%20time%20and%20labor%20so%20I%20chose%20not%20to%20take%20on%20a%20larger%20debt%20by%20utilizing%20the%20FHA%20203(k)%20option.%20I%20purchased%20the%20home%20with%20a%20tenant%20residing%20in%20one%20of%20the%20units%20and%20I%20lived%20in%20the%20other.%20I%20also%20wanted%20the%20tenant%20to%20cover%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20mortgage%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Consider%20refinancing%20your%20loan%20for%20your%20next%20property%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20tenant%20able%20to%20pay%20close%20to%20my%20entire%20mortgage%20%E2%80%94%20%241%2C000%20of%20the%20%241%2C150%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20home%20valued%20higher%20than%20what%20I%20was%20purchasing%20it%20for%2C%20I%20became%20the%20owner%20of%20my%20very%20first%20owner-occupied%20rental%20property.%20Since%20purchasing%20my%20first%20owner-occupied%20investment%20property%20in%202008%2C%20I've%20used%20Zillow%20to%20source%20qualified%20tenents%20and%20a%20local%20landlord%20association%20for%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20later%2C%20with%20my%20first%20property%20completely%20updated%20and%20rents%20increased%20to%20fair%20market%20rent%20(%241%2C200)%2C%20I%20refinanced%20my%20loan%20to%20conventional%20lending.%20This%20allowed%20me%20to%20identify%20another%20property%20I%20purchased%20within%20FHA%20guidelines%3A%20a%20three-bedroom%2C%20single-family%20home%2C%C2%A0which%20I%20purchased%20within%20the%20guidelines%20of%20a%20conventional%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsinglefamily.fanniemae.com%2Foriginating-underwriting%2Fmortgage-products%2Fhomestyle-renovation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFannie%20Mae%20HomeStyle%20Renovation%20Loan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20HomeStyle%20Renovation%20Loan%20applies%20to%20a%20one%20to%20four-unit%20primary%20residence%2C%20a%20one-unit%20second%20home%2C%20or%20a%20one-unit%20investment%20property.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebalancemoney.com%2Ffannie-mae-homestyle-loan-vs-203-k-what-s-the-difference-5223385%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20difference%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20this%20type%20of%20loan%20is%20that%205%25%20of%20the%20total%20loan%20is%20required%20as%20a%20down%20payment%2C%20and%20it%20often%20comes%20with%20a%20higher%20interest%20rate%2C%20which%20at%20the%20time%20of%20my%20purchase%20was%205.75%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202015%2C%20as%20it%20applies%20to%20utilizing%20FHA%20financing%20to%20acquire%20properties%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20have%20purchased%20our%20dream%20home%20%E2%80%94%20a%201771%20farmhouse%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20two-family%20second%20home%20as%20a%20beach%20rental%20investment%20property.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Be%20aware%20of%20a%20few%20caveats%20with%20FHA%20financing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20while%20there's%20no%20limit%20on%20a%20borrower%20utilizing%20an%20FHA%20loan%2C%20you%20can't%20have%20two%20loans%20running%20concurrently%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20must%20be%20your%20intention%20to%20live%20in%20the%20property%20you're%20financing%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20to%20continue%20purchasing%20income%20properties%20with%20an%20FHA%20loan%2C%20the%20loan%20underwriter%20must%20be%20satisfied%20that%20you're%20establishing%20a%20new%20primary%20residence%20more%20than%20100%20miles%20from%20the%20prior%20residence%C2%A0or%20relocating%20for%20employment-related%20reasons%2C%20that%20your%20family%20size%20is%20increasing%20(to%20house%20additional%20children%20or%20family%20members)%2C%20that%20there's%20a%20non-occupying%20co-borrower%20(you're%20buying%20for%20an%20aging%20parent%2C%20then%20yourself)%2C%20or%20you're%20vacating%20a%20co-owned%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20purchase%20of%20our%20forever%20home%2C%20we%20overcame%20this%20challenge%20by%20refinancing%20our%20two-family%20home%20with%20a%20conventional%20mortgage%2C%20so%20that%20an%20FHA%20loan%20could%20be%20used.%20Having%20a%20second%20home%20is%20a%20qualifying%20term%2C%20so%20this%20was%20not%20a%20big%20obstacle%20to%20overcome.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20take%20the%20leap%2C%20run%20through%20different%20scenarios.%20Know%20the%20price%20you're%20willing%20to%20pay%3B%20what%20the%20down%20payment%20will%20come%20to%3B%20the%20interest%20rate%3B%20rent%20you%20plan%20to%20charge%20by%20referring%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fdatasets%2Ffmr.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHUD's%20Office%20of%20Policy%20Development%20and%20Research%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20what%20homeowner's%20insurance%20you'll%20need.%20Finally%2C%20factor%20in%20what%20money%20you'll%20set%20aside%20for%20repairs%20and%20vacancy%2C%20what%20your%20cash%20flow%20will%20be%2C%20and%20what%20costs%20are%20associated%20with%20a%20refinance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20another%20warning%3A%20occupancy%20fraud%20is%20a%20very%20real%20thing.%20Avoid%20this%20at%20all%20costs%2C%20not%20only%20do%20you%20expose%20yourself%20to%20having%20the%20loan%20recalled%20by%20your%20lender%2C%20but%20breaking%20the%20terms%20of%20an%20FHA%20mortgage%20without%20permission%20from%20the%20lender%20can%20result%20in%20serious%20legal%20and%20financial%20consequences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Take%20the%20time%20to%20invest%20in%20yourself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERead%2C%20research%2C%20and%20network%20with%20other%20investors%2C%20local%20bankers%2C%20and%20hard-money%20lenders.%20Also%2C%20learn%20about%20purchasing%20homes%20through%20unconventional%2C%20creative%20terms.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterest%20rates%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Fmortgages%2Ffha-loan-rates%2F%3FmortgageType%3DPurchase%26partnerId%3Dbr3%26pid%3Dbr3%26pointsChanged%3Dfalse%26purchaseDownPayment%3D88000%26purchaseLoanTerms%3D30yr%252C5-1arm%252C5-6arm%26purchasePoints%3DAll%26purchasePrice%3D440000%26purchasePropertyType%3DSingleFamily%26purchasePropertyUse%3DPrimaryResidence%26searchChanged%3Dfalse%26ttcid%26userCreditScore%3D780%26userDebtToIncomeRatio%3D0%26userFha%3Dfalse%26userVeteranStatus%3DNoMilitaryService%26zipCode%3D06114%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enow%20higher%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20when%20I%20first%20started%20investing%20in%202008.%C2%A0Don't%20let%20this%20be%20a%20deterrent.%20Do%20your%20homework%2C%20know%20your%20numbers%2C%20and%20if%20done%20correctly%2C%20you'll%20pass%20the%20rate%20increase%20off%20in%20rents%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20my%20success%2C%20there%20are%20some%20things%20I%20would've%20done%20differently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20change%20in%20retrospect%20would've%20been%20to%20maximize%20the%20unit%20count%20within%20the%20FHA%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20increasing%20my%20unit%20count%20from%20two%20to%20four%20%E2%80%94%20after%20meeting%20the%20one-year%20owner-occupied%20residency%20requirement%20and%20refinancing%20the%20property%20to%20conventional%20financing%20%E2%80%94%20I%20could've%20then%20identified%20a%20smaller%20two%20or%20three-family%20property%20to%20own%20or%20occupy.%20My%20borrowing%20allowance%20would've%20been%20higher%2C%20allowing%20me%20to%20identify%20another%20property%20within%20the%20FHA%20guidelines.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20wh