22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Row%3A%20Looking%20for%20%E2%80%98Character%E2%80%99%20When%20History%20Establishes%20it%20Unequivocally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20or%20more%20precisely%2C%20north%20India%2C%20has%20been%20gripped%20by%20a%20frenzy.%20A%20frenzy%20of%20temple%20construction.%20Even%20more%20obnoxious%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20latter%20bit%20is%20being%20accomplished%20by%20staking%20claim%20upon%20existing%20mosques.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECourts%20in%20India%2C%20which%20should%20ideally%20be%20the%20sentinels%20of%20the%20constitutional%20doctrine%20of%20secularism%2C%20are%20actively%20aiding%20and%20abetting%20such%20acts.%20Three%20decades%20ago%2C%20Justice%20J.S.%20Verma%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fjonew%2Fjudis%2F10197.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0pronounced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20Hinduism%20is%20not%20a%20religion%20but%20a%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20%E2%80%98de-religiosification%E2%80%99%20allowed%20the%20forces%20of%20Hindutva%20to%20pose%20Hinduism%20as%20a%20supra-religious%20order%20that%20naturally%20makes%20available%20to%20its%20adherents%2C%20unquestionably%2C%20the%20best%20moral%20code%20of%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20judgment%20made%20the%20term%20immune%20from%20scrutiny%20under%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2096%2F5%2Fa1951-43.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20deemed%20the%20use%20of%20religion%20in%20elections%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98corrupt%20practice%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%E2%80%93Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20combine%20has%20made%20the%20best%20use%20of%20this.%20From%20Advani%20to%20Modi%2C%20all%20have%20shielded%20themselves%20from%20the%20allegations%20of%20political%20usage%20of%20Hinduism%20by%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20not%20a%20religion%20but%20a%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fallahabad-high-court-green-lights-gyanvapi-suit%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Justice%20R.R.%20Agarwal%20of%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20on%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20issue%20has%20opened%20a%20Pandora%E2%80%99s%20Box.%20In%20an%20act%20of%20legal%20acrobatics%2C%20Justice%20Agarwal%20has%20found%20a%20new%20way%20to%20undermine%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F1922%3Flocale%3Den%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndia%2520Code%253A%2520Places%2520of%2520Worship%2520(Special%2520Provisions)%2520Act%252C%25201991%26text%3DLong%2520Title%253A%2Cconnected%2520therewith%2520or%2520incidental%2520thereto.%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20unequivocally%20stipulates%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ethe%20maintenance%20of%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20it%20existed%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20its%20Ram%20Mandir%20judgment%2C%20had%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%98%E2%80%98%3Ci%3Ethe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20is%20intrinsically%20related%20to%20the%20obligations%20of%20a%20secular%20state.%20It%20reflects%20the%20commitment%20of%20India%20to%20the%20equality%20of%20all%20religions%E2%80%A6%20%5BT%5Dhe%20law%20speaks%20to%20our%20history%20and%20the%20future%20of%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3ECognisant%20as%20we%20are%20of%20our%20history%20and%20of%20the%20need%20for%20the%20nation%20to%20confront%20it%2C%20independence%20was%20a%20watershed%20moment%20to%20heal%20the%20wounds%20of%20the%20past%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20remembered%20that%20when%20the%20Bill%20was%20being%20debated%2C%20some%20BJP%20members%20of%20Parliament%20(MPs)%20questioned%201947%20as%20the%20cut-off%20date%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20real%20cut-off%20date%20should%20be%20the%2012th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Agarwal%20in%20his%20judgment%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20has%20the%20prerogative%20to%20define%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ereligious%20character%20of%20the%20place%20of%20worship%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20further%20said%20that%20the%20plaintiffs%20have%20not%20demanded%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Econversion%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20hence%20it%20is%20a%20title%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20wonders%20what%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20a%20mosque%2C%20temple%20or%20church%20may%20be%2C%20if%20not%20a%20mosque%2C%20temple%20and%20church%2C%20respectively.%20Justice%20Agarwal%20seems%20to%20be%20making%20an%20undue%20distinction%20between%20forms%20of%20worship%20practised%20in%20the%20place%20of%20worship%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20%E2%80%98character%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20said%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cambridge%20Dictionary%20defines%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98character%E2%80%99%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ethe%20particular%20combination%20of%20qualities%20in%20someone%20or%20something%20that%20makes%20them%20or%20it%20different%20from%20others%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20this%20definition%2C%20a%20mosque%20has%20a%20combination%20of%20architectural%2C%20ritualistic%2C%20and%20religious%20qualities%20quite%20different%20from%20a%20temple%20or%20a%20church%2C%20which%20makes%20its%20character%20distinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20syncretic%20history%20of%20India%20has%20examples%20of%20mosques%20being%20constructed%20in%20the%20Hindu%20architectural%20style.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Cheraman%20Juma%20Mosque%20in%20Kodungallur%2C%20the%20oldest%20mosque%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20had%20hanging%20oil-lit%20lamps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20still%20burns%20an%20oil%20lamp%20which%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20over%201%2C000%20years%20old.%20People%20of%20all%20faiths%20bring%20oil%20for%20the%20lamp%20as%20an%20offering%2C%20thereby%20underlining%20the%20secular%20and%20pluralistic%20tradition%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20example%20of%20pluralistic%20Indian%20tradition%20that%20is%20often%20forgotten%20is%20the%20Sikh%20Guru%20Arjan%20Dev%E2%80%99s%20invitation%20to%20Mian%20Hazrat%20Mir%2C%20a%20Muslim%20Sufi%20saint%2C%20to%20lay%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20the%20Golden%20Temple%20in%20Amritsar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20Justice%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20judgment%2C%20one%20wonders%20what%20the%20%E2%80%98religious%20character%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Cheraman%20Juma%20Mosque%20and%20the%20Golden%20Temple%20would%20be%20if%20not%20a%20mosque%20and%20a%20gurudwara%20respectively%20adorned%20by%20a%20centuries-old%20quilt%20of%20syncretism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20has%20done%20nothing%20but%20fanned%20the%20fires%20of%20communal%20notoriety.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20injunction%20to%20the%20lower%20court%20to%20deliver%20its%20final%20judgment%20within%20six%20months%20has%20chimed%20with%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%20This%20is%20nothing%20but%20the%20biggest%20cause%20of%20worry%20for%20all%20secular%20forces%20in%20the%20country%2C%20especially%20the%20biggest%20religious%20minority%20of%20India%E2%80%94%20the%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20whole%20business%20of%20temple%20construction%20and%20mosque%20destruction%20has%20at%20its%20base%20the%20logic%20of%20authoritative%20majoritarianism.%20India%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20this.%20Turkey%E2%80%99s%20strongman%20leader%20Recep%20Erdogan%20also%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2FidUSKBN24B1TH%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0marked%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20conversion%20of%20the%20Hagia%20Sophia%20into%20a%20mosque%20as%20a%20great%20step%20towards%20reclaiming%20the%20lost%20glory%20of%20the%20Ottoman%20caliphate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20between%20India%20and%20Turkey%20is%20that%20such%20acts%20in%20the%20latter%20would%20not%20endanger%20the%20existence%20of%20religious%20minorities.%20Turkey%20is%20a%2099%20percent%20Sunni%20Muslim%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20Muslims%20account%20for%2014.5%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20(approximately%2020%20crore%20in%20number)%20and%20account%20for%2011%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20population.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20ramifications%20would%20be%20much%20larger%20and%20harsher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20question%20of%20%E2%80%98historical%20mistakes%E2%80%99.%20It%20must%20be%20understood%20that%20Mughal%20India%20was%20not%20a%20democratic%20State%20with%20mass-participatory%20democracy.%20Aurangzeb%20did%20not%20contest%20elections.%20Rulers%2C%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20ruled%20by%20the%20sword.%20State%20policy%20was%20nothing%20but%20the%20monarch%E2%80%99s%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20destruction%20of%20the%20temples%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20Mathura%20and%20Thatta%20had%20deep%20political%20reasons.%20Mathura%20was%20for%20long%20the%20region%20of%20the%20Jat%20peasantry%E2%80%99s%20rebellion%20against%20the%20extractive%20Mughal%20State.%20Another%20reason%20for%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20wrath%20towards%20Mathura%E2%80%99s%20Krishna%20Dev%20temple%20was%20that%20it%20had%20been%20patronized%20by%20Dara%20Shukoh%2C%20his%20major%20rival%20for%20the%20throne.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Saqi%20Mustaid%20Khan%2C%20a%20historian%20who%20wrote%20after%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EIn%201669%20the%20king%20learned%20that%20at%20Benares%2C%20deviant%20Brahmins%20were%20teaching%20false%20books%20at%20their%20established%20schools.%20Curious%20seekers%E2%80%94%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20alike%E2%80%94%20traveled%20great%20distances%20to%20gain%20depraved%20knowledge%20from%20them%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorian%20and%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20latest%20biographer%20Audrey%20Truschke%20has%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianculturalforum.in%2F2018%2F08%2F14%2Faudrey-truschke-aurangzeb-indian-history%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0noted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EAurangzeb%20evinced%20concern%20with%20elite%20Brahmins%20deceiving%20common%20Hindus%20about%20their%20own%20religion%20and%20was%20perhaps%20especially%20alarmed%20that%20Muslims%20were%20falling%20prey%20to%20charlatans%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mughals%20had%20given%20grants%20to%20many%20temples.%20Aurangzeb%20himself%20had%20given%20grants%20and%20gifts%20to%20Hindu%20temples.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20his%20ninth%20year%20of%20reign%2C%20Aurangzeb%20conferred%20land%20upon%20the%20Umananda%20Temple%20in%20Guwahati%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201687%2C%20the%20emperor%20gave%20some%20empty%20land%20on%20a%20ghat%20in%20Benares%20(which%20was%2C%20incidentally%2C%20near%20a%20mosque)%20to%20Ramjivan%20Gosain%20to%20build%20houses%20for%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Epious%20Brahmins%20and%20holy%20faqirs%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201691%2C%20Aurangzeb%20conferred%20eight%20villages%20and%20a%20sizable%20chunk%20of%20tax-free%20land%20on%20Mahant%20Balak%20Das%20Nirvani%20of%20Chitrakoot%20to%20support%20the%20Balaji%20Temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201698%2C%20he%20gifted%20rent-free%20land%20to%20a%20Brahmin%20named%20Rang%20Bhatt%20in%20eastern%20Khandesh%20in%20central%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20goes%20on%20and%20includes%20temples%20and%20individuals%20in%20Allahabad%2C%20Vrindavan%2C%20Bihar%20and%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20if%20Indian%20Muslims%20started%20retaliating%20against%20the%20temple%20frenzy%20of%20the%20Hindus%20by%20demanding%20the%20re-possession%20of%20land%20grants%20to%20Hindu%20temples%20by%20the%20Mughals.%20India%20would%20not%20be%20a%20liveable%20place%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShubham%20Sharma%20is%20a%20research%20scholar%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20University%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20US.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-row-looking-for-character-when%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Leaflet.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704024017000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-row-looking-for-character-when-history-establishes-it-unequivocally%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%E2%80%98de-religiosification%E2%80%99%20of%20Hinduism%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20judiciary%20has%20allowed%20the%20forces%20of%20Hindutva%20to%20pose%20Hinduism%20as%20a%20supra-religious%20order%20that%20naturally%20makes%20available%20to%20its%20adherents%2C%20unquestionably%2C%20the%20best%20moral%20code%20of%20conduct.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-row-looking-for-character-when-history-esta