2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20the%20risk%20of%20further%20disconnecting%20us%20the%20same%20way%20hybrid%20work%20initially%20did%20because%20if%20everybody's%20just%20interacting%20with%20AI%20all%20the%20time%2C%20we%20forget%20how%20to%20work%20with%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-want-soft-skills-good-communication-teamwork-leadership-energetic-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esoft%20skills%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20empathy%2C%20and%20teamwork%20will%20become%20even%20more%20important%20as%20AI%20takes%20over%20aspects%20of%20our%20jobs.%20In%20effect%2C%20people%20will%20be%20left%20to%20do%20the%20stuff%20humans%20are%20best%20at%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20could%20make%20us%20hungry%20for%20human%20connection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI's%20move%20into%20the%20workplace%20doesn't%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be%20a%20bad%20thing.%20Of%20course%2C%20it%20could%20give%20a%20big%20boost%20to%20productivity%20and%20save%20us%20from%20some%20of%20the%20more%20mundane%20yet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpact-of-out-of-hour-emails-employee-wellbeing-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estress-inducing%20tasks%20like%20email%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20somehow%20fill%20our%20days%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20points%20to%20a%20potential%20bright%20spot%3A%20All%20of%20this%20interaction%20with%20AI%20could%20make%20us%20more%20hungry%20for%20the%20real%20thing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfordmartin.ox.ac.uk%2Fblog%2Fjobs-will-be-automated-but-not-because-of-the-latest-generative-ai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehuman%20connection%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20a%20view%20shared%20by%20Andr%C3%A9%20Martin%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWrong%20Fit%2C%20Right%20Fit.%26quot%3B%20He%20told%20BI%20that%20AI%20could%20free%20up%20time%20for%20leaders%2C%20for%20example%2C%20by%20taking%20over%20some%20of%20the%20drudgery%20that's%20a%20part%20of%20most%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20AI%20could%20get%20rid%20of%20some%20of%20those%20administrative%20tasks%2C%20it%20actually%20opens%20up%20the%20door%20for%20us%20to%20have%20deeper%2C%20richer%2C%20better%20connections%2C%20more%20innovation%2C%20more%20collaboration%2C%20more%20time%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0if%20we%20choose%20to%20put%20it%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%20One%20danger%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20if%20AI%20takes%20over%20more%20of%20our%20jobs%2C%20we%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-boost-income-side-hustles-multiple-jobs-eighty-billion-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadd%20to%20our%20to-do%20lists%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20find%20ways%20to%20connect%20with%20others%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20lack%20of%20connection%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0not%20just%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20a%20worry%20for%20many%20of%20us%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Finternet%2F2022%2F03%2F17%2Fhow-americans-think-about-artificial-intelligence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%20from%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%202022.%20The%20snapshot%2C%20which%20involved%20about%2010%2C000%20people%2C%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Black%20of%20human%20connection%2C%20qualities%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20No.%203%20reason%20that%20those%20worried%20about%20AI%20cited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20workers%20aren't%20tied%20in%20with%20each%20other%2C%20it%20can%20be%20bad%20for%20the%20bottom%20line.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foffice-friendship-dead-remote-work-employers-turnover-great-resignation-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPeople%20who%20have%20work%20friends%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20stick%20with%20a%20job%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they're%20also%20more%20productive%2C%20engaged%2C%20satisfied%20in%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%20less%20stressed%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20might%20connect%20with%20peers%20more%20if%20work%20gets%20less%20boring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20by%20stripping%20away%20some%20of%20the%20drudgery%20at%20work%2C%20we'd%20not%20only%20have%20more%20time%2C%20but%20we'd%20also%20be%20more%20willing%20to%20get%20to%20know%20our%20coworkers.%20Martin%20said%20having%20too%20many%20meetings%20on%20our%20calendars%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwednesday-most-popular-day-work-meetings-avoid-overload-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emake%20us%20too%20focused%20on%20tasks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20less%20willing%20to%20ask%20our%20coworkers%20about%20their%20days%20or%20how%20we%20might%20help%20them%20fix%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20problems%20that%20can't%20be%20solved%20by%20an%20AI%20copilot%2C%20we%20might%20do%20well%20to%20turn%20to%20colleagues%20for%20help%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0maybe%20even%20by%2C%20gasp%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpick-up-your-phone-like-boomers-good-for-health-loneliness%3F_gl%3D1*djftjk*_ga*OTIwODQ1Njk3LjE2NjY4Nzc5NTU.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMzcxMDEyOS42MjYuMS4xNzAzNzEwMjg1LjU1LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epicking%20up%20the%20phone%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20calling%20them.%20That%20human%20interaction%20can%20help%20make%20us%20less%20lonely.%20That's%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-loneliness-does-to-the-body-and-brain-2023-12%3F_gl%3D1*1l9ayc9*_ga*OTIwODQ1Njk3LjE2NjY4Nzc5NTU.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMzcxMDEyOS42MjYuMC4xNzAzNzEwMTM2LjUzLjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econnecting%20with%20others%20is%20a%20biological%20necessity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20surprising%20benefit%20that%20AI%20at%20work%20could%20bring.%20It%20might%20make%20us%20feel%20respected%2C%20Vladimir%20Lukic%2C%20global%20leader%2C%20tech%20and%20digital%20advantage%2C%20at%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%2C%20told%20BI.%20This%20might%20come%20down%20to%20simple%20things%20like%20workers%20believing%20an%20employer%20is%20using%20AI%20to%20make%20their%20jobs%20easier%20or%20just%20to%20remain%20competitive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20stay%20in%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20conducted%20in%20part%20by%20BCG%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fpublications%2F2022%2Fthe-value-of-ai-for-individuals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecompanies%20draw%20benefits%20from%20AI%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20their%20workers%20also%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20companies%20that%20were%20embedding%20it%20had%20the%20most%20engaged%20workforce%20and%20highest%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20Lukic%20told%20BI%2C%20referring%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20engagement%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20result%20in%20happier%20employees%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20in%20workers%20whom%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-employees-happy-strategies-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecolleagues%20rate%20more%20favorably%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20teammates.%20Maybe%20that%20will%20help%20fight%20off%20loneliness%20on%20the%20job%20even%20as%20we%20work%20alongside%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-lonelier-at-work-friends-connect-with-coworkers-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704022381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658d908cec62ab5daf7f3489%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-lonelier-at-work-friends-connect-with-coworkers-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Artificial%20intelligence%20could%20make%20us%20lonelier%20on%20the%20job.%20But%20it%20could%20give%20us%20more%20time%20to%20connect%20with%20coworkers%2C%20and%20make%20us%20hungrier%20for%20human%20connection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-lonelier-at-work-friends-connect-with-coworkers-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222023%3A%20A%20Year%20of%20Ironies%20and%20Paradoxes%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22153154%2Fsrinagar-2740020_1920.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202023%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20a%20year%20full%20of%20ironies%2C%20paradoxes%20and%20blatant%20double%20standards%20%E2%80%94%20all%20packaged%20and%20sold%20under%20the%20name%20of%20economic%20progress%2C%20democracy%20and%20normalcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20for%20example%20the%20issue%20of%20elections%2C%20which%20the%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20last%20saw%20nine%20years%20ago%20in%202014.%20The%20Union%20government%20is%20perhaps%20acutely%20aware%20of%20what%20conducting%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20in%20a%20Muslim-majority%20region%20would%20mean%20%E2%80%93%20a%20complete%20ouster%20from%20being%20able%20to%20direct%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%20(assuming%20that%20statehood%20will%20be%20restored).%20So%20it%20has%20devised%20a%20new%20stratagem.%20It%20has%20put%20out%20ceremonial%20statements%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20emphasising%20the%20indispensability%20of%20holding%20elections%20to%20the%20legislature%2C%20but%20without%20actually%20proceeding%20to%20hold%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20talk%20and%20less%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20election%20commissioner%20pledged%20that%20polls%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20are%20due%20and%20would%20be%20held%20after%20taking%20the%20weather%20and%20security%20concerns%20into%20account.%20The%20following%20month%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20voter%20list%20is%20about%20to%20be%20finalised.%20After%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20will%20take%20a%20call%20on%20holding%20polls.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20acknowledged%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20a%20vacuum%20in%20the%20Union%20Territory%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20filled%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20said%20that%20the%20qualifying%20date%20for%20the%20revision%20of%20electoral%20rolls%20for%20the%20UT%20was%20to%20precede%20the%20national-level%20special%20summary%20revision%20(SSR)%20%E2%80%93%20as%20if%20to%20convey%20the%20seriousness%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20part%20to%20restore%20democracy%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20the%20Commission%20extended%20the%20date%20for%20filing%20claims%20and%20objections%20on%20SSR%2C%20and%20a%20month%20later%2C%20the%20Divisional%20Commissioner%20of%20Kashmir%20was%20holding%20meetings%20to%20%E2%80%9Creview%20the%20progress%20achieved%E2%80%9D.%20In%20July%2C%20Lt%20Governor%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Manoj%20Sinha%20appointed%20Braj%20Raj%20Sharma%2C%20retired%20IAS%20officer%2C%20as%20the%20state%20election%20commissioner.%20Yet%20another%20intent%20of%20good%20faith%2C%20perhaps%3F%20In%20September%2C%20Sinha%20went%20on%20to%20claim%20that%20if%20elections%20were%20held%20now%2C%20%E2%80%9CEighty%20percent%20of%20the%20people%20will%20vote%20and%20favour%20the%20prevailing%20system%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20despite%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20its%20submission%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20August%2C%20which%20was%20hearing%20the%20Article%20370%20case%2C%20saying%20that%20polls%20can%20be%20held%20%E2%80%98any%20time%20now%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20refused%20to%20set%20a%20time%20frame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it%20took%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20finalise%20September%202024%20as%20the%20deadline%20for%20holding%20the%20assembly%20polls.%20So%20one%20might%20genuinely%20ask%2C%20what%20role%20was%20the%20government%20playing%20all%20along%2C%20except%20for%20prevaricating%20over%20the%20issue%20of%20holding%20elections%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMother%20of%20ironies%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20bitter%20irony%20of%202023%20was%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Raj%20Bhawan%20commemorating%20West%20Bengal%20Statehood%20Day%20in%20June%20even%20as%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20own%20statehood%20remains%20forfeited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20also%20the%20year%20when%20people%20started%20to%20realise%20the%20adverse%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20legal%20changes%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20status%20enacted%20pursuant%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20Article%20370%20in%20August%202019%20were%20going%20to%20affect%20them.%20In%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20government%20sent%20bulldozers%20fanning%20out%20across%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20UT%20to%20raze%20the%20properties%20it%20claimed%20have%20been%20built%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cencroached%E2%80%9D%20State%20land.%20In%20one%20case%2C%20a%20petitioner%20had%20moved%20the%20JK%20and%20Ladakh%20high%20court%20arguing%20that%20he%20could%20get%20his%202%2C000%20square%20feet%20of%20proprietary%20land%20exchanged%20in%20lieu%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekahcharai%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(grazing)%20land%20that%20he%20was%20accused%20of%20holding%20%E2%80%9Cillegally%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20he%20was%20right%20because%20the%20laws%20that%20existed%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20before%202019%20permitted%20for%20such%20an%20exchange.%20But%20judges%20had%20to%20set%20his%20petition%20aside%20as%20Section%20133(2)%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Land%20Revenue%20Act%2C%201996%20which%20legitimised%20such%20allowances%20no%20longer%20existed%20in%20its%20previous%20form%2C%20thereby%20making%20the%20petitioner%20as%20well%20as%20thousands%20of%20other%20%E2%80%9Cencroachers%E2%80%9D%20vulnerable%20to%20expulsion%2C%20with%20their%20properties%20liable%20to%20be%20bulldozed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuch%20ado%20about%20nothing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20was%20showcasing%20the%20mounting%20tourist%20numbers%20as%20evidence%20of%20normalcy%20and%20economic%20growth%2C%20it%20simultaneously%20slashed%20the%20duties%20on%20apple%20imports%20from%20the%20US%20and%20Iran.%20With%20the%20apple%20yield%20of%2017%20lakhs%20metric%20tonnes%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20accounts%20for%2075%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20apple%20production.%20And%20for%20all%20the%20talk%20of%20it%20being%20a%20boon%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20tourism%20contributes%20only%206%25%20to%20the%20UT%E2%80%99s%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20it%20is%20the%20agriculture%2C%20trade%20and%20allied%20sectors%20that%20are%20the%20major%20drivers%20of%20growth%20in%20Kashmir.%20But%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20waive%20surcharges%20of%20imported%20apples%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20impact%20the%20Kashmiri%20growers%20adversely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDispensing%20justice%20selectively%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20ironies%20have%20abounded%20in%202023.%20Take%20for%20example%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20(SIA)%2C%20a%20nodal%20unit%20for%20the%20National%20Investigation%20Agency%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20to%20trace%20out%20the%20perpetrators%20involved%20in%20the%20militancy%20incidents%20taking%20place%20during%20the%201990s.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20whole%20campaign%2C%20the%20SIA%20also%20reopened%20the%20case%20of%20Retired%20Justice%20Neelkanth%20Ganjoo%2C%20who%20was%20among%20the%20first%20to%20be%20killed%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20insurgency%20in%201989.%20The%20SIA%20also%20arrested%20two%20absconding%20militants%2033%20years%20later%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20assassination%20of%20Kashmiri%20religious%20leader%20Mirwaiz%20Moulvi%20Farooq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20nothing%20happens%20in%20Kashmir%20without%20it%20being%20part%20of%20the%20overall%20optics.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20asserting%20time%20and%20again%20that%20it%20wants%20to%20put%20the%20history%20of%20insurgency%20behind%20and%20start%20a%20new%20chapter.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20perhaps%20that%20it%20can%20only%20go%20so%20far%20in%20this%20attempt.%20As%2066-year-old%20Abdul%20Rashid%20Baba%2C%20brother%20of%20one%20of%20the%2067%20persons%20who%20died%20in%20the%20massacre%20following%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20killing%2C%20told%20one%20journalist%2C%E2%80%9DWhat%20about%20justice%20for%20us%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20think%20about%20the%20case%20of%20Army%20Major%20Bhoopendera%20Singh%20of%2062%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20(RR)%20whose%20sentence%20was%20suspended%20by%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20Tribunal%20that%20also%20granted%20him%20bail.%20Singh%20was%20involved%20in%20extra-judicial%20killings%20(locally%20called%20fake%20encounters)%20in%20Ashimpora%20Shopian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20incidents%20like%20these%20occurring%20every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20the%20government%20exposes%C2%A0itself%20to%20the%20allegations%20of%20being%20insincere%20and%20duplicitous%2C%20especially%C2%A0when%20it%E2%80%99s%20making%20vaunted%C2%A0claims%20of%20being%20committed%20towards%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20and%20civil%20freedoms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20civil%20freedoms%2C%20the%20year%202023%20was%20hardly%20dissimilar%20to%20previous%20years.%20The%20arrest%20of%20journalist%20and%20editor%20Irfan%20Mehraj%20brought%20into%20sharp%20focus%20what%20critics%20have%20called%20the%20appalling%20press%20freedom%20conditions%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20also%20stepped%20up%20the%20passport%20policing%20of%20journalists%20and%20politicians%20who%20tend%20to%20be%20critical%20of%20its%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fnews%2Findian-government-strips-passports-kashmiri-dissent-modi%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMiddle%20East%20Eye%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20at%20least%20seven%20Kashmiris%20living%20overseas%20have%20had%20their%20passports%20suspended%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20they%20are%20a%20threat%20to%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20a%20special%20NIA%20court%20in%20Srinagar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwaheed-parra-travel-ban-jammu-kashmir-yale-pdp%5C%22%3Edenied%20permission%20to%20Waheed%20ur%20Rehman%20Para%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20political%20leader%20from%20South%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Pulwama%20region%2C%20from%20travelling%20to%20the%20United%20States%20to%20attend%20the%20Yale%20Peace%20Fellowship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20some%20of%20these%20decisions%20reached%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%2C%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20grounds%20for%20withholding%20or%20suspending%20passports%20were%20set%20aside%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%E2%80%99s%20octogenarian%20mother%2C%20Gulshan%20Nazir%20where%20the%20judges%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmehbooba-mufti-passport-denied-national-security%5C%22%3Epromptly%20ordered%20that%20her%20passport%20be%20released%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20criticising%20the%20authorities%20for%20acting%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmouthpiece%20of%20CID%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20authorities%20at%20Kashmir%20University%20removed%20works%20of%20authors%20such%20as%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%20and%20Basharat%20Peer%20from%20the%20curriculum%2C%20in%20yet%20another%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20dissenting%20views%20inside%20institutions%20of%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20website%20and%20its%20social%20media%20handles%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmedia-bodies-condemn-govts-action-blocking-website-social-media-handles-of-the-kashmir-walla%5C%22%3Ewere%20blocked%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20instructions%20of%20the%20government.%20Separately%2C%20the%20editors%20of%20the%20publication%20were%20served%20eviction%20notices%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20relinquish%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20was%20any%20good%20news%20pertaining%20to%20press%20freedom%20in%202023%2C%20it%20was%20the%20bail%20order%20served%20to%20three%20incarcerated%20Kashmiri%20journalists.%20But%20that%20intervention%20came%20from%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitancy%20on%20decline%20but%20dangers%20remain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20militancy%20is%20concerned%2C%20it%20has%20been%20a%20pretty%20peaceful%20year%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley.%20The%20hit-and-run%20killings%20that%20had%20spiked%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20came%20down%2C%20if%20not%20getting%20completely%20eradicated.%20The%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20data%20shared%20with%3Cem%3E%C2%A0The%20Wire%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eindicates%20a%20precipitous%20decline%20of%20local%20recruitment%20which%20stands%20out%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20developments%20of%202023.%20The%20local%20recruitment%20has%20come%20down%20from%20122%20in%202020%2C%20155%20in%202021%2C%20119%20in%202022%20and%2022%20in%202023.%20172%20militants%20were%20killed%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20last%20year%2C%20while%20this%20year%20the%20number%20stands%20at%20113.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20aspect%20has%20gone%20hand-in-hand%20with%20increasing%20foreign%20participation.%20As%20General%20Officer%20Commanding-in-Chief%20(GOC-in-C)%20Northern%20Command%20Lieutenant%20General%20Upendra%20Dwivedi%20said%20in%20September%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20insurgency%20began%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnumber%20of%20foreign%20terrorists%20killed%20is%20four-times%20higher%20than%20local%20terrorists%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20shifting%20dynamic%20which%20is%20resulting%20in%20the%20Jammu%20region%20becoming%20the%20new%20epicentre%20of%20violence%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%20This%20year%2C%20at%20least%2034%20soldiers%20have%20died%20in%20various%20militant%20attacks%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20of%20which%2020%20alone%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20two%20districts%20of%20Rajouri%20and%20Poonch%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20casualties%20among%20the%20armed%20forces%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20perhaps%20for%20this%20reason%20why%20General%20Officer%20Commanding%20of%20Chinar%20Corps%20(GOC)%20Lieutenant%20General%20A.D.S.%20Aujla%20remarked%20that%20the%20time%20was%20not%20yet%20ripe%20for%20the%20Army%20to%20move%20to%20barracks%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20in%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20BJP%20government%E2%80%99s%20discourse%20around%20normalcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fjk-terror-spike-prompts-relook-at-pre-winter-strategy-deployment-8967257%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20spurt%20in%20terror%20incidents%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20where%20infiltration%20peaks%20before%20the%20onset%20of%20winter%2C%20has%20prompted%20security%20forces%20to%20reassess%20their%20counter-terror%20strategy%20in%20the%20Union%20Territory%2C%20and%20plans%20to%C2%A0%20redistribute%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20(RR)%20units%20might%20not%20be%20implemented%20immediately%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202023%20thus%20offers%20a%20subtle%20reminder%20that%20the%20BJP%20continues%20to%20uphold%20its%20most%20cherished%20mantra%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20governing%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20running%20with%20th